CharVehicle.Name: XFT Disseminator

Character.Story: Xiaan grew up on Coruscant where her father was a minor politician, and her mother was politically active. Although he played no major role, her father was vocally opposed to the Empire. [P] About 10 years ago, when Xiaan was 15 years old, her family was attacked and her mother, father and younger brother were killed. Xiaan managed to escape and stowed away on a ship leaving Coruscant. On board the ship was a man (human) called Jack, who was a skillful, but aging bounty hunter. [P] Although she cannot prove it, Xiaan is convinced that the Empire was behind the attack. [P] [B]Motivation:[b] [P] Understandably, Xiaan despises everything to do with the Empire. She would love to avenge her family, but that would mean killing the people that pulled the strings, not just those that "pulled the trigger". And that she considers as impossible. [P] So instead she contents herself with taking every opportunity to hurt the Empire in any way possible. Her dream is to become a real thorn in the side of the Empire. [P] [B]Obligations:[b] [P] She is in debt to Jack for everything he did for her. He taught her everything he knows, and was like a father to her after she lost her family. Now he is retired and she feels obligated (gladly) to support him, and protect him if necessary. [P] Unknown to Jack, Xiaan borrowed money from Timo the Hutt to pay off some of Jack's old gambling debts. She did this so that he could retire without too much fear of the past catching up with him. [P] [B]Bounty Hunters Creed:[b] [P] Jack taught Xiaan to honor the bounty hunters creed. In particular: you either capture or kill. [P] [B]Personality:[b] [P] Due to her charisma, Xiaan is a natural leader. But, she dislikes authority, and rebels against it. So on the one hand she may be destined to lead, on the other hand, that is the last thing she wants. This can result in a certain amount of internal conflict. [P] Xiaan is an interesting mix of hot and cold. Hot because she is not afraid to use her female charms. Cold because she is relatively immune to the charms of others. [P] But she is also hot and cold in other ways. For example she is not immune to making rash decisions, especially if she gets angry. Although this seldom happens. However she is always cool (even when angry!). Nothing can phase her, and she is able to think clearly even in very tight situations. [P] So besides her natural talent for using a rifle, her coolness is the main thing that makes her a good bounty hunter. [P] [B]Xiaan and Teemo the Hutt:[b] [P] In her last job for Teemo, Xiaan was charged with bringing back the head of an alien named "the Gecko", who had cheated the Hutt. Surprisingly, the Gecko surrendered and so Xiaan brought him back alive. Teemo then refused to pay Xiaan because he said that she had not fulfilled the contract (the Gecko was still alive). So Xiaan drew her blaster pistol and blew the Geckos head off (she no longer considered him her prisoner). [P] She then asked for payment, but the Hutt still refused because he said he did not ask for the Geckos brains all over his floor! He said this would be a lesson to her to do as contracted in the first place. [P] At this point Xiaan leveled the blaster pistol at Teemo saying the Gecko died by her hand, so she wanted her payment. At that moment the Hutt opened a trap-door beneath her feet (of course, she should have known!), and Xiaan winged him with the blaster before she fell into the trap. [P] Teemo then told her that she would now serve him as an exotic dancer until her debt was paid off! [P] Fortunately, Xiaan managed to escape this fate worse than death, and that is where our story began...

MoralityPair.Notes: Xiaan feals a compulsion to just do better, at certain things, she had a tough childhood...
